deliberations. By highlighting the value tensions and trade-offs and examining the impact that the design of the deliberations has on policy and the creation of conditions that encourage exchange, the contributors aim to build capacity within our institutions and society to find new ways to discuss and solve complex problems.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political ideologies / Democracy.2bisacsh  apublic consultation, public deliberation, wicked problems, citizenship, civic engagement, environment.1 aHanson, Lorelei L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKahane, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781771992169423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781771992169/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles